SPEEDSTERS are wanted to obey the rules of the road of face
the music in Ekurhuleni around the Alberton and Edenvale area. EMPD spokeswoman Lieutenant Colonel Kelebogile Thepa said
last month the Ekurhuleni Metro Police Department (EMPD) received news from the
Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) that, the requested application, to enforce
the Law using mobile and fixed speed cameras, became successful and it is
approved. READ: Joburg speedsters answer to no one! Thepa said, “Even though the locations or spots where speed
cameras will be fully operational will not be revealed, motorists are advised
to drive at an appropriate speed, keep a safe following distance and to obey
rules of the road, especially in and around the Alberton, Edenvale and Kempton
Park areas. “The EMPD Officers, will be operating mobile and static
speed cameras, in different locations where the speed limit sign fixed, is 60,
70, 80 and 120km/h, conducting speed checks in order to stop Speedsters from
being reckless and negligent, on our roadways.” The Enforcement will be effective from Wednesday 01 June
2022, until 31 May 2023.